comments: LLS shows during Rubio's (UTA) drive, Westbrook (OKC) makes clean contact with the ball.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Ingles (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ingles (UTA) briefly places an arm on George's (OKC) back but immediately slides it off and the contact does not affect his FOM.
Adams (OKC) establishes a screening position in Ingles' (UTA) path and initiates some arm contact with Ingles, but he is able to move through the contact.
Ingles (UTA) places an arm to the front of George (OKC) during the inbound but the contact is marginal.
[Observable in enhanced video] George (OKC) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
[Observable in enhanced video] Adams (OKC) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Ferguson (OKC) makes marginal contact to the body of Mitchell (UTA) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
RLB shows Grant (OKC) cleanly deflects the loose ball away from Gobert (UTA).  Any contact to the body following the deflection is considered incidental.
Adams (OKC) dislodges Gobert (UTA) from his position during the rebound.
Gobert (UTA) has his arms extended when he sets the screen on Ferguson (OKC), but the contact is marginal and he does not push him.
Ferguson (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Mitchell (UTA) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
George (OKC) and Mitchell (UTA) make incidental contact with each other on the perimeter and are both able to move through the contact.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact to the arm of Westbrook (OKC) during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact to the arm of Grant (OKC) during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
George (OKC) makes marginal contact with Mitchell (UTA) defending him on the perimeter that does not affect his SQBR.
Grant (OKC) cleanly blocks Mitchell's (UTA) driving shot attempt.
LLS shows Mitchell (UTA) makes some contact to Grant's (OKC) arm/body as he is falling to the floor, but the contact does not affect his ability to make the pass.
Westbrook (OKC) makes contact to the arm of Mitchell (UTA) on the drive that affects his SQBR.
George (OKC) briefly wraps his arm around Ingles (UTA) as he deflects the ball away but the contact does not prevent Ingles from getting to the pass.
George (OKC) makes incidental contact with Rubio (UTA) while the ball is loose.
Mitchell (UTA) gets his hand on the ball and then makes incidental contact with George (OKC) during the rebound.
Adams (OKC) firms up his screening position in Mitchell's (UTA) path and does not deliver the contact.
Mitchell (UTA) briefly places his arm to Westbrook's (OKC) side during the pick but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Grant (OKC) makes marginal contact with Mitchell (UTA) during his drive to the basket.  When Mitchell enters his shooting motion, Mitchell leans forward and initiates the contact.
Crowder (UTA) beats Westbrook (OKC) to the spot, establishing himself in a legal guarding position in his path and Westbrook drives through him.
Crowder (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Grant (OKC) and he absorbs the contact.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Nader (OKC) and he absorbs the contact.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Mitchell (UTA) loses control of the ball out of bounds.
Adams (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Ingles (UTA) and he does not deliver the contact.
Ingles (UTA) briefly places an arm around Adams (OKC) during the screen but he immediately removes it and does not affect his FOM.
[Observable in enhanced video] Adams (OKC) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Crowder (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Grant (OKC) and absorbs the contact.  The two players briefly engage and disengage following the screen.
Nader (OKC) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Mitchell (UTA) that does not affect his drive to the basket.
Nader (OKC) makes marginal contact with Gobert's (UTA) arm going for the rebound that does not affect his tip-in shot attempt.
Rubio (UTA) moves along Schroder's (OKC) path to the basket and makes incidental contact with him that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) and Adams (OKC) make incidental contact with each other during the rebound.  Adams begins to lose his balance and falls to the floor.
Ingles (UTA) briefly places an arm to the front of George (OKC) on the perimeter but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Crowder (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Grant (OKC) and absorbs the contact.
George (OKC) and Crowder (UTA) briefly engage and separate off ball.
LAR shows Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position from a wide stance, but the contact with George (OKC) is initiated to his upper body and he does not deliver any leg-to-leg contact.
Grant (OKC) makes contact to the arm of Gobert (UTA) during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Adams (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Rubio's (UTA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver the contact.
Crowder (UTA) firms up his screening position in Nader's (UTA) path and he does not deliver the contact.
Ingles (UTA) does not go through Adams' (OKC) space and dislodge him from his position on the perimeter.
Adams (OKC) absorbs the contact from Ingles (UTA) on the perimeter and does not affect his ability to make the pass.
LAR shows George (OKC) is still moving laterally into Gobert (UTA) at the time of the contact and he trips Gobert, affecting his ability to establish position in the lane.
RLB and LAR show George (OKC) make contact to Gobert's (UTA) arm and affect his putback dunk attempt.
Schroder (OKC) has his arm extended when he makes contact with Rubio (UTA) but he does not dislodge him from his position.
Crowder (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Grant (OKC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Adams (OKC) makes marginal contact with Gobert (UTA) that does not affect his ability to defend Grant's (OKC) shot attempt.
Rubio (UTA) makes contact with Adams' (OKC) arm and affects his ability to gather the rebound.  The foul occurs prior to Adams having control of the ball and this is a non-shooting foul.
Adams (OKC) and Gobert (UTA) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Crowder (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Grant (OKC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Adams (OKC) makes incidental contact with Gobert (UTA) that does not affect his ability to get to the rebound.
Ingles (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Grant's (OKC) path and has his arms slightly extended, but the contact is marginal.
[Observable in enhanced video] Adams (OKC) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Nader (OKC) makes marginal contact with Mitchell (UTA) that does not affect his SQBR on the driving shot attempt.
Grant (OKC) makes brief contact with the net but it does not affect Mitchell's (UTA) shot attempt or its ability to be scored.
LLS shows Adams (OKC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Gobert (UTA) during rebounding.
Adams (OKC) briefly grasps Gobert's (UTA) jersey but does not affect his ability to get to the rebound.
Rubio (UTA) avoids making contact with George (OKC) when he reaches in prior to the shot attempt.
LLB and RAR show Adams (OKC) legally contests Korver's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
